<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session  
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251</b> 
<b>OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Brazil:  draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>2006/&#8230; The right of everyone to the realization of the highest  
attainable standard of physical and mental health 
</b></p>
<p> <i>The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i> Recalling</i> all resolutions concerning the realization of the right of everyone to the 
enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of physical and mental health adopted by the 
Commission on Human Rights, 
</p>
<p> <i>Bearing in mind </i>paragraph 6 of General Assembly resolution 60/251 of 
15 March 2006 establishing the Human Rights Council, 
</p>
<p> <i>Requests</i> the Special Rapporteur on the right of everyone to the enjoyment of the 
highest attainable standard of physical and mental health, within his existing mandate, to 
report to the Human Rights Council at its fourth session on the realization of the right of 
everyone to the enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of physical and mental health, 
trying in particular to identify and explore, from the perspective of the right to the highest 
attainable standard of health, the key features of an effective, integrated and accessible health 
system. 
</p>
<p><b>----- 
</b></p>
